1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:36,168 --> 00:01:38,448
You invited me for tea
up on Mount Baiyun?

3
00:01:40,487 --> 00:01:42,368
That doesn't sound like something
you'd do.

4
00:01:44,888 --> 00:01:46,248
Liang Danning.

5
00:01:47,088 --> 00:01:48,608
Out with it now.

6
00:01:48,968 --> 00:01:50,608
Fine, I'll be straight with you.

7
00:01:52,047 --> 00:01:53,927
Li Dongming made me get you there.

8
00:01:54,248 --> 00:01:57,088
He's waiting at Moxingling
and going to propose to you.

9
00:02:03,407 --> 00:02:04,767
Why are you not even surprised?

10
00:02:05,168 --> 00:02:07,047
Did you already know?

11
00:02:07,368 --> 00:02:08,287
Last week,

12
00:02:08,287 --> 00:02:11,127
I found a jewelry receipt
in his coat pocket.

13
00:02:12,727 --> 00:02:13,407
But it's fine.

14
00:02:13,407 --> 00:02:14,328
I'm good at acting.

15
00:02:14,768 --> 00:02:16,407
I can fake being shocked.

16
00:02:46,287 --> 00:02:47,488
I need to talk to you.

17
00:02:49,287 --> 00:02:50,887
Get off. Let's walk around.

18
00:02:54,727 --> 00:02:55,528
What a shame.

19
00:02:55,528 --> 00:02:56,727
It's a bit foggy.

20
00:02:57,567 --> 00:03:00,607
Otherwise,
you can see the whole skyline from here.

21
00:03:07,447 --> 00:03:10,167
I got married at 23

22
00:03:10,328 --> 00:03:11,528
to Yao Xiaohui.

23
00:03:11,968 --> 00:03:15,248
I thought
a programmer like him was honest

24
00:03:15,248 --> 00:03:16,368
and faithful.

25
00:03:16,847 --> 00:03:18,048
Turns out he was a gambler.

26
00:03:19,048 --> 00:03:19,968
Anyway,

27
00:03:21,007 --> 00:03:22,048
I've been through it.

28
00:03:22,287 --> 00:03:24,208
So I have some advice for you.

29
00:03:28,248 --> 00:03:28,928
Go ahead.

30
00:03:30,048 --> 00:03:31,048
Brace yourself.

31
00:03:32,768 --> 00:03:34,768
I don't think
Li Dongming is marriage material.

32
00:03:35,928 --> 00:03:36,368
Yes,

33
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:38,447
he's successful,

34
00:03:38,768 --> 00:03:39,768
comes from a good family,

35
00:03:39,768 --> 00:03:41,127
and treats you well.

36
00:03:41,648 --> 00:03:44,048
But I've seen him
at multiple nightclubs more than once.

37
00:03:44,887 --> 00:03:46,088
I know it's for work,

38
00:03:46,368 --> 00:03:48,167
but he's surrounded
by too many temptations.

39
00:03:48,768 --> 00:03:50,127
Plus, he's quite charming.

40
00:03:51,488 --> 00:03:52,607
He won you over, didn't he?

41
00:03:55,607 --> 00:03:57,248
He has a friend, Xiao Yang,

42
00:03:57,928 --> 00:03:58,528
who hit on me.

43
00:03:59,287 --> 00:04:00,488
Just one time,

44
00:04:00,488 --> 00:04:02,287
but I knew the guy was married.

45
00:04:02,928 --> 00:04:06,328
Birds of a feather flock together.

46
00:04:06,887 --> 00:04:08,808
Marrying Li Dongming is risky for you.

47
00:04:10,607 --> 00:04:12,607
I've been at GST for years,

48
00:04:13,928 --> 00:04:16,448
going to nightclubs
like going to my own living room.

49
00:04:17,047 --> 00:04:20,008
I've seen as many players
as Li Dongming has.

50
00:04:21,888 --> 00:04:23,927
There've been ambiguous moments,
inevitably.

51
00:04:24,847 --> 00:04:28,607
I can't promise
I've always stayed clear-headed either.

52
00:04:29,568 --> 00:04:32,088
But Li Dongming gets how my job works.

53
00:04:32,888 --> 00:04:34,448
When I'm at nightclubs,

54
00:04:34,768 --> 00:04:37,167
he never video calls me.

55
00:04:37,648 --> 00:04:39,008
We're frank

56
00:04:39,607 --> 00:04:40,607
about where we're going

57
00:04:40,768 --> 00:04:41,968
and who we're meeting.

58
00:04:42,487 --> 00:04:47,008
We both know
how to balance work and life.

59
00:04:47,528 --> 00:04:48,407
So do you love him?

60
00:04:48,648 --> 00:04:50,968
Of course, I love him.

61
00:04:51,487 --> 00:04:52,247
Why?

62
00:04:57,128 --> 00:04:58,008
I think

63
00:04:58,807 --> 00:05:02,487
we're both fiercely ambitious.

64
00:05:04,128 --> 00:05:05,807
We talk about work constantly.

65
00:05:06,768 --> 00:05:10,128
We can spend whole nights
talking about work.

66
00:05:11,607 --> 00:05:13,727
We give advice

67
00:05:14,287 --> 00:05:15,448
to each other.

68
00:05:15,888 --> 00:05:18,528
Plus, he's not bad-looking.

69
00:05:19,648 --> 00:05:21,648
And he makes good money.

70
00:05:21,648 --> 00:05:22,367
Alright, enough.

71
00:05:22,528 --> 00:05:23,768
Save your confession

72
00:05:23,768 --> 00:05:25,768
for when he proposes.

73
00:05:25,768 --> 00:05:26,807
Tell him directly then.

74
00:05:30,367 --> 00:05:33,088
So you have "approved" my marriage?

75
00:05:34,328 --> 00:05:35,287
What choice do I have?

76
00:05:35,487 --> 00:05:36,727
What can I do?

77
00:05:36,847 --> 00:05:38,367
I have to approve.

78
00:05:40,768 --> 00:05:41,768
But you must be happy.

79
00:05:46,568 --> 00:05:47,807
Sure, I will be happy.

80
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:48,727
I promise.

81
00:06:00,008 --> 00:06:04,104
=Episode 14=
(Provocation)

82
00:06:08,088 --> 00:06:09,927
When are you confronting Li Dongming?

83
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:13,167
I haven't decided yet.

84
00:06:14,768 --> 00:06:17,927
My lawyer says
I need to trace his assets before filing

85
00:06:18,407 --> 00:06:19,247
for divorce.

86
00:06:20,008 --> 00:06:23,247
Plus, my promotion
is hanging in the balance.

87
00:06:25,008 --> 00:06:25,487
Right,

88
00:06:26,648 --> 00:06:28,968
he actually helps your career a lot.

89
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:32,128
That's the cruel irony.

90
00:06:34,008 --> 00:06:38,607
Part of me is grateful for his support,

91
00:06:41,287 --> 00:06:42,128
but another part

92
00:06:43,688 --> 00:06:46,367
can't stand imagining him
with other women.

93
00:06:47,807 --> 00:06:50,008
It's kind of...

94
00:06:50,927 --> 00:06:51,927
Love and hate?

95
00:06:55,688 --> 00:06:56,487
Hard to describe.

96
00:07:00,487 --> 00:07:01,927
But I know he doesn't love me

97
00:07:04,927 --> 00:07:05,727
anymore.

98
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:10,607
But you still love him.

99
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:19,648
Or you wouldn't be so sad.

100
00:07:37,367 --> 00:07:38,487
It'll be okay.

101
00:08:05,047 --> 00:08:06,328
Mom, Dad,

102
00:08:06,328 --> 00:08:07,008
Zhao Mei.

103
00:08:07,008 --> 00:08:07,688
You're back.

104
00:08:07,688 --> 00:08:08,487
I'm back.

105
00:08:10,888 --> 00:08:11,927
Just in time for dinner.

106
00:08:11,927 --> 00:08:13,367
Mom, look what I brought for you.

107
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:14,367
What is this?

108
00:08:14,487 --> 00:08:15,047
What is it?

109
00:08:15,047 --> 00:08:16,367
You had time to shop?

110
00:08:16,568 --> 00:08:18,688
Zhao Mei said you love this pastry.

111
00:08:18,688 --> 00:08:20,487
She reminded me to buy it for you.

112
00:08:20,487 --> 00:08:22,688
Okay, thank you, Zhao Mei.

113
00:08:23,367 --> 00:08:24,568
I'll take this inside for you.

114
00:08:24,568 --> 00:08:25,167
Okay.

115
00:08:25,607 --> 00:08:26,568
Open it and eat.

116
00:08:26,568 --> 00:08:28,367
Dad, come out and have some pastry.

117
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:43,247
This is for you.

118
00:08:45,487 --> 00:08:47,847
Why is it trendy to bring gifts
from business trips lately?

119
00:08:48,247 --> 00:08:49,328
It means you're on my mind.

120
00:08:56,007 --> 00:08:57,367
You also bought it at the airport?

121
00:08:58,127 --> 00:09:00,247
I bought it at the mall
next to the hotel in Shanghai.

122
00:09:00,808 --> 00:09:02,007
What do you mean by "also"?

123
00:09:03,127 --> 00:09:05,928
Xinghualou has a branch
at the Guangzhou airport.

124
00:09:06,568 --> 00:09:07,968
It says so on the packaging.

125
00:09:11,247 --> 00:09:12,048
Mom.

126
00:09:12,127 --> 00:09:13,607
I need to use this bag.

127
00:09:13,607 --> 00:09:16,568
I need this bag to put something in.

128
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:20,808
I was just teasing you.

129
00:09:21,247 --> 00:09:23,607
The packaging is the same
in Guangzhou and Shanghai.

130
00:09:24,007 --> 00:09:26,208
I didn't expect
you'd actually buy it at the airport.

131
00:09:27,168 --> 00:09:28,928
But yours was really bought in Shanghai.

132
00:09:28,928 --> 00:09:31,048
I have the receipt here.

133
00:09:31,928 --> 00:09:32,527
I believe you.

134
00:09:33,247 --> 00:09:34,007
Zhao Mei.

135
00:09:34,487 --> 00:09:36,247
Where is the cooking wine?

136
00:09:37,487 --> 00:09:39,527
Mom, the cooking wine might be all gone.

137
00:09:39,647 --> 00:09:40,847
I'll get you whiskey.

138
00:09:43,887 --> 00:09:44,607
Zhao Mei,

139
00:09:44,607 --> 00:09:46,487
aren't you supposed to resign?

140
00:09:46,487 --> 00:09:47,568
Why did you go back?

141
00:09:48,887 --> 00:09:51,247
Later, the company
offered me a really good deal.

142
00:09:51,247 --> 00:09:52,247
So I couldn't leave.

143
00:09:53,127 --> 00:09:53,808
I see.

144
00:09:54,088 --> 00:09:55,527
But to be honest,

145
00:09:55,527 --> 00:09:58,048
that's not a good company for women.

146
00:09:58,607 --> 00:09:59,968
Even if you don't want children,

147
00:10:00,088 --> 00:10:02,367
you shouldn't drink so much
for the sake of your health.

148
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:02,968
Mom.

149
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,607
When you first met Zhao Mei,
she was doing this job.

150
00:10:05,607 --> 00:10:06,288
You shut up.

151
00:10:07,127 --> 00:10:07,847
Stay out of this.

152
00:10:08,607 --> 00:10:09,968
I'm talking to Zhao Mei.

153
00:10:17,007 --> 00:10:19,127
Actually, it's not
that I don't want to find a job.

154
00:10:19,607 --> 00:10:21,767
It's just that jobs aren't easy to find.

155
00:10:24,247 --> 00:10:26,847
And recently,
there have been layoffs everywhere.

156
00:10:27,288 --> 00:10:29,487
Dongming's company
is doing layoffs right now.

157
00:10:31,007 --> 00:10:31,688
Don't look at me.

158
00:10:31,968 --> 00:10:33,127
They won't lay me off.

159
00:10:34,208 --> 00:10:35,847
But don't be too complacent.

160
00:10:36,127 --> 00:10:37,408
The female analyst,

161
00:10:37,408 --> 00:10:38,847
the one who works with you.

162
00:10:39,007 --> 00:10:41,007
Didn't you say you would fire her?

163
00:10:41,487 --> 00:10:42,767
Which female analyst?

164
00:10:42,887 --> 00:10:43,767
The one

165
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:45,127
who posted your photo.

166
00:10:45,127 --> 00:10:46,527
I asked you about her before.

167
00:10:47,208 --> 00:10:48,607
She's quite pretty.

168
00:10:49,088 --> 00:10:50,968
Dongming even took her to play golf.

169
00:10:53,007 --> 00:10:54,208
It's not what she said.

170
00:10:54,208 --> 00:10:55,928
She's just an ordinary subordinate.

171
00:10:56,367 --> 00:10:57,408
It was a business event.

172
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:01,607
Yes, don't overthink it.

173
00:11:01,607 --> 00:11:04,607
Nowadays, it's common for a male boss
to take a female subordinate

174
00:11:04,607 --> 00:11:05,767
to play golf.

175
00:11:06,007 --> 00:11:07,408
It's not good to take a man.

176
00:11:07,727 --> 00:11:08,288
Exactly.

177
00:11:15,968 --> 00:11:16,928
An ordinary subordinate?

178
00:11:17,208 --> 00:11:18,968
It's no big deal to fire her.

179
00:11:20,607 --> 00:11:21,887
In the end, was she laid off?

180
00:11:23,127 --> 00:11:23,887
No.

181
00:11:23,887 --> 00:11:24,767
No?

182
00:11:26,647 --> 00:11:27,928
Someone did worse than she did.

183
00:11:29,168 --> 00:11:30,527
It's okay if she wasn't fired.

184
00:11:31,088 --> 00:11:32,767
Otherwise, she would be quite pitiful.

185
00:11:32,887 --> 00:11:33,928
That's nonsense.

186
00:11:34,127 --> 00:11:35,887
Survival of the fittest
in the workplace.

187
00:11:36,127 --> 00:11:38,408
Incompetent employees
should be eliminated.

188
00:11:39,007 --> 00:11:41,688
Your mindset is really modern.

189
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:00,887
Dad,

190
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:02,088
what is it?

191
00:12:02,088 --> 00:12:02,847
Go ahead.

192
00:12:05,288 --> 00:12:08,208
You and Zhao Mei are good?

193
00:12:08,487 --> 00:12:09,088
Sure, we are.

194
00:12:09,527 --> 00:12:14,007
Then why was her attitude so strange
when she mentioned that girl?

195
00:12:16,007 --> 00:12:16,767
Here's the thing.

196
00:12:17,247 --> 00:12:20,367
I once took that female subordinate
to a business golf event.

197
00:12:20,568 --> 00:12:22,808
Then this girl posted about it
on her social media.

198
00:12:22,928 --> 00:12:24,808
Zhao Mei saw the photo.

199
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:27,647
She just got jealous over nothing.

200
00:12:28,168 --> 00:12:29,607
I thought it was all over.

201
00:12:29,607 --> 00:12:31,487
Who knew she'd bring it up again today?

202
00:12:33,808 --> 00:12:34,568
Dongming,

203
00:12:35,328 --> 00:12:36,568
although I've stepped down now,

204
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:42,367
I witnessed too many similar situations
when I was in office.

205
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:43,647
I know

206
00:12:44,647 --> 00:12:47,367
your career is quite successful now.

207
00:12:47,887 --> 00:12:50,288
I hope you can discipline yourself.

208
00:12:51,007 --> 00:12:54,127
The more successful a man becomes
in his career,

209
00:12:54,247 --> 00:12:56,968
the more crucial it is
to prevent any family troubles.

210
00:12:57,607 --> 00:12:59,727
Otherwise, arguments, fights,

211
00:13:00,127 --> 00:13:01,168
or even divorce

212
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:05,208
will drain your energy,

213
00:13:05,607 --> 00:13:06,808
waste your time,

214
00:13:07,288 --> 00:13:09,168
and hinder your progress.

215
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:11,808
Sacrificing long-term stability

216
00:13:12,127 --> 00:13:13,887
for momentary pleasure

217
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:16,088
is simply not worth it.

218
00:13:16,968 --> 00:13:20,568
Zhao Mei may not be the best woman,

219
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:26,367
but you married her
after careful consideration.

220
00:13:27,007 --> 00:13:30,887
I hope you'll take responsibility
for your choice.

221
00:13:31,767 --> 00:13:33,887
Dad, I'm a grown man.

222
00:13:34,247 --> 00:13:35,727
I understand what you're saying.

223
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,487
I hope so.

224
00:13:45,527 --> 00:13:46,088
Danning,

225
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:47,288
are you free?

226
00:13:47,288 --> 00:13:48,048
Let's meet up.

227
00:13:48,727 --> 00:13:50,727
I'm flying back
to Guangzhou late tonight.

228
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:53,007
You pick a day,
tomorrow or the day after?

229
00:13:53,607 --> 00:13:54,968
Great! Tomorrow morning, then.

230
00:13:55,607 --> 00:13:56,328
So urgent?

231
00:13:56,847 --> 00:13:57,928
Is it about Zhao Mei?

232
00:13:59,568 --> 00:14:00,456
Let's talk in person.

233
00:14:01,048 --> 00:14:03,408
Don't tell Zhao Mei I contacted you.

234
00:14:04,007 --> 00:14:04,408
Okay.

235
00:14:04,847 --> 00:14:05,367
Bye.

236
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:09,487
Finished your run already?

237
00:14:10,007 --> 00:14:11,767
Qi Youlan just called me.

238
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:14,007
She scheduled an interview
with me for tomorrow morning.

239
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:15,288
I rushed back to prepare.

240
00:14:15,288 --> 00:14:15,808
Really?

241
00:14:16,007 --> 00:14:17,727
Let me find out who's interviewing you.

242
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:19,647
Seems like someone surnamed Xu.

243
00:14:19,647 --> 00:14:20,408
Xu Jia?

244
00:14:21,887 --> 00:14:23,647
Is your period over?

245
00:14:29,607 --> 00:14:31,847
The Ruijin Consulting team arrived
at 8:45 AM.

246
00:14:32,487 --> 00:14:33,647
I chatted with that girl.

247
00:14:33,808 --> 00:14:35,288
They worked overtime until 3 AM.

248
00:14:35,727 --> 00:14:37,048
They only slept four hours total.

249
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:39,408
They worked too hard.

250
00:14:40,007 --> 00:14:41,288
How many people did they send?

251
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:42,367
Just one.

252
00:14:42,727 --> 00:14:43,928
Their people are valuable.

253
00:14:43,928 --> 00:14:45,127
They bill by the hour.

254
00:14:45,647 --> 00:14:46,647
One is enough.

255
00:14:55,247 --> 00:14:57,487
This is an analyst
from Ruijin Consulting.

256
00:14:57,767 --> 00:14:58,536
This is Zhao Mei.

257
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:00,247
Hello, Ms. Zhao.

258
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:10,288
You two chat.

259
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:14,448
My business card.

260
00:15:22,127 --> 00:15:24,527
I thought
the scheduled interviewer was Miss Xu.

261
00:15:25,127 --> 00:15:28,887
Yes, but she suddenly felt unwell,
so I'm stepping in temporarily.

262
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:37,367
I watched your speech video before.

263
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:38,767
It was excellent.

264
00:15:39,887 --> 00:15:41,000
I shared it on my Moments.

265
00:15:49,088 --> 00:15:50,048
Shall we begin?

266
00:15:50,847 --> 00:15:51,328
No rush.

267
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:54,968
I need to input your information first.

268
00:15:55,767 --> 00:15:56,767
May I add you on WeChat?

269
00:15:57,288 --> 00:15:59,144
I'll send you the link
and verification code.

270
00:15:59,527 --> 00:16:00,367
Shall I scan you?

271
00:16:09,328 --> 00:16:10,168
Please add me.

272
00:16:20,408 --> 00:16:21,568
We're starting the recording.

273
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,048
I will ask you some questions.

274
00:16:24,288 --> 00:16:26,168
If you feel
any questions are inappropriate,

275
00:16:26,168 --> 00:16:27,088
you can interrupt me.

276
00:16:27,408 --> 00:16:29,704
(Li Dongming, guess who's interviewing me?)
Or you can refuse to answer.

277
00:16:37,247 --> 00:16:37,847
It's starting.

278
00:16:49,968 --> 00:16:50,367
Hey.

279
00:16:52,247 --> 00:16:53,607
One Americano, please. Thanks.

280
00:16:53,767 --> 00:16:54,288
Okay.

281
00:17:05,247 --> 00:17:06,007
Spill it.

282
00:17:06,527 --> 00:17:07,448
What is it?

283
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:12,408
Is Zhao Mei seeing someone else?

284
00:17:14,007 --> 00:17:15,247
Are you out of your mind?

285
00:17:15,247 --> 00:17:16,247
Answer my question.

286
00:17:16,247 --> 00:17:17,688
Watch your attitude.

287
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:20,527
Setting aside
whether that's true or not,

288
00:17:21,247 --> 00:17:23,487
what makes you think
I'd tell you if I knew?

289
00:17:23,487 --> 00:17:24,807
Your reaction tells me the truth.

290
00:17:25,368 --> 00:17:26,287
You have no clue.

291
00:17:27,487 --> 00:17:28,128
Nonsense.

292
00:17:28,128 --> 00:17:29,128
There is no someone else.

293
00:17:29,368 --> 00:17:30,168
I hope so.

294
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:32,727
But my intuition is usually right.

295
00:17:33,368 --> 00:17:34,287
Something's wrong.

296
00:17:34,287 --> 00:17:34,888
How so?

297
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:35,688
That's it.

298
00:17:36,287 --> 00:17:37,487
Has she said anything to you?

299
00:17:39,608 --> 00:17:41,408
Help me figure out who it could be.

300
00:17:41,408 --> 00:17:42,848
Who does she usually interact with?

301
00:17:43,368 --> 00:17:45,047
Colleagues? Or clients?

302
00:17:45,527 --> 00:17:46,968
You know how I am with her.

303
00:17:46,968 --> 00:17:47,888
I'm so good to her.

304
00:17:48,007 --> 00:17:49,527
She can't do anything to betray me.

305
00:17:51,168 --> 00:17:51,968
What's so funny?

306
00:17:54,487 --> 00:17:56,128
I'm laughing at how ridiculous you are.

307
00:17:59,128 --> 00:17:59,888
First,

308
00:18:00,936 --> 00:18:02,344
Zhao Mei isn't having an affair.

309
00:18:02,767 --> 00:18:05,247
She has never done anything
to betray you.

310
00:18:05,247 --> 00:18:07,567
Second, I'd like to remind you.

311
00:18:08,368 --> 00:18:10,007
Don't do anything to betray Zhao Mei.

312
00:18:10,688 --> 00:18:12,208
What could I possibly do?

313
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:13,928
Li Dongming, have we just met today?

314
00:18:14,688 --> 00:18:15,688
What are you implying?

315
00:18:15,968 --> 00:18:17,968
Even if I occasionally flirt outside,

316
00:18:17,968 --> 00:18:20,047
it's just socializing, just an act.

317
00:18:20,247 --> 00:18:22,327
I'm not like some men
who actually play for real.

318
00:18:23,807 --> 00:18:25,047
What's with the sarcasm?

319
00:18:26,648 --> 00:18:28,767
I heard you conquered Shen Mo.

320
00:18:29,287 --> 00:18:30,247
He seems quite serious.

321
00:18:30,608 --> 00:18:31,448
He's a big shot.

322
00:18:32,007 --> 00:18:32,608
Congrats.

323
00:18:36,487 --> 00:18:37,368
Next question.

324
00:18:38,208 --> 00:18:41,047
What value
does your current work bring you?

325
00:18:41,688 --> 00:18:43,888
You need to be careful
with questions like this.

326
00:18:44,247 --> 00:18:46,247
The focus is on you.

327
00:18:47,007 --> 00:18:49,968
You can't just talk about the value
you bring to the company.

328
00:18:50,168 --> 00:18:51,007
That sounds too fake.

329
00:18:51,327 --> 00:18:54,168
It also makes it seem like
you don't really love the job.

330
00:18:54,688 --> 00:18:58,487
You have to say
what benefits this job gives you.

331
00:19:00,327 --> 00:19:03,168
That way,
when the bosses throw us under the bus,

332
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:04,727
they'll feel even less guilty.

333
00:19:05,287 --> 00:19:08,327
I started as an ordinary promoter.

334
00:19:09,247 --> 00:19:11,527
From promoter to supervisor,

335
00:19:12,007 --> 00:19:14,287
to manager, and then to Deputy Director,

336
00:19:15,247 --> 00:19:17,567
step by step,
I've gotten to where I am today.

337
00:19:19,968 --> 00:19:21,807
I know what I should do.

338
00:19:23,487 --> 00:19:25,487
I also know what I shouldn't do.

339
00:19:31,848 --> 00:19:33,807
But not everyone understands that.

340
00:19:38,408 --> 00:19:39,408
Are you going off-topic?

341
00:19:39,408 --> 00:19:42,287
No, I'm not going off-topic.

342
00:19:43,767 --> 00:19:45,047
You just haven't understood.

343
00:19:47,487 --> 00:19:48,567
In short,

344
00:19:49,968 --> 00:19:52,087
it's a sense of control.

345
00:19:53,928 --> 00:19:54,807
A thrill.

346
00:19:57,567 --> 00:19:58,648
You're saying

347
00:19:58,968 --> 00:20:02,168
your current work gives you a thrill?

348
00:20:03,007 --> 00:20:03,688
Exactly.

349
00:20:06,487 --> 00:20:08,368
My work gives me a thrill.

350
00:20:15,168 --> 00:20:15,648
And you?

351
00:20:18,247 --> 00:20:20,688
Does your work give you a thrill?

352
00:20:32,247 --> 00:20:33,087
Just asking.

353
00:20:41,192 --> 00:20:42,448
(Personal growth and values;
Balancing family and career)

354
00:20:42,448 --> 00:20:43,287
Next question.

355
00:20:43,688 --> 00:20:45,007
As a married woman,

356
00:20:45,527 --> 00:20:47,968
how do you balance career and family?

357
00:20:49,247 --> 00:20:50,968
You should skip this question.

358
00:20:50,968 --> 00:20:52,527
It's such a boring question.

359
00:20:53,247 --> 00:20:56,128
Do you ask male interviewees
the same thing?

360
00:20:59,247 --> 00:21:00,128
We didn't before.

361
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:01,368
Now we do.

362
00:21:04,727 --> 00:21:05,247
Okay.

363
00:21:06,968 --> 00:21:08,087
My answer is,

364
00:21:08,648 --> 00:21:10,327
I don't need to consciously balance it.

365
00:21:11,247 --> 00:21:13,688
I have full control over my time.

366
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:17,968
Do you plan
to have children in the next five years?

367
00:21:20,767 --> 00:21:22,807
That question is inappropriate,
isn't it?

368
00:21:26,007 --> 00:21:28,007
If your company's HR asks this,

369
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:29,192
it'll be inappropriate.

370
00:21:29,408 --> 00:21:30,968
But I can ask because there's

371
00:21:31,528 --> 00:21:33,168
no employment relationship between us.

372
00:21:33,168 --> 00:21:33,688
Of course,

373
00:21:34,527 --> 00:21:35,527
you can refuse to answer.

374
00:21:39,168 --> 00:21:39,688
No.

375
00:21:42,247 --> 00:21:45,487
I have no plans
to have children in the next five years.

376
00:21:47,007 --> 00:21:47,807
Give me your reason.

377
00:21:49,168 --> 00:21:52,128
I can't shoulder the responsibility
of raising a child.

378
00:21:52,487 --> 00:21:54,968
The risks are too high,
the responsibility too heavy.

379
00:21:56,208 --> 00:21:57,007
Bad answer.

380
00:21:57,247 --> 00:22:00,928
It makes you seem irresponsible

381
00:22:00,968 --> 00:22:02,047
and afraid of risk.

382
00:22:03,767 --> 00:22:05,848
Then I really don't know how to answer.

383
00:22:06,487 --> 00:22:08,327
The question itself is malicious.

384
00:22:09,648 --> 00:22:12,287
Let's not question the question itself.

385
00:22:12,648 --> 00:22:13,688
It's pointless.

386
00:22:13,928 --> 00:22:17,287
I'll give you a better answer.

387
00:22:17,527 --> 00:22:18,327
(For example...)

388
00:22:20,968 --> 00:22:24,327
Now isn't the best time
for me to raise a child.

389
00:22:25,087 --> 00:22:27,567
I still have many dreams to fulfill.

390
00:22:27,968 --> 00:22:32,128
So currently,
I prefer to focus on myself.

391
00:22:38,287 --> 00:22:38,848
What?

392
00:22:41,788 --> 00:22:43,048
(Paused)

393
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:50,128
I've seen this exact answer
in our system.

394
00:22:58,928 --> 00:22:59,727
Next question.

395
00:23:02,968 --> 00:23:03,767
What do you mean?

396
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:04,767
I've started recording.

397
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:06,807
I know. I'm asking what you mean.

398
00:23:11,168 --> 00:23:12,567
How long will this interview take?

399
00:23:14,648 --> 00:23:15,287
One hour.

400
00:23:15,848 --> 00:23:17,128
Should be over in half an hour.

401
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:21,247
I felt some of the earlier questions
were a bit repetitive.

402
00:23:21,247 --> 00:23:22,487
So I...

403
00:23:23,247 --> 00:23:24,047
It should be okay.

404
00:23:24,527 --> 00:23:25,287
You talk to her.

405
00:23:29,287 --> 00:23:31,208
Say again what you just said.

406
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:32,208
Record it.

407
00:23:34,007 --> 00:23:34,767
You forgot?

408
00:23:34,968 --> 00:23:38,368
You said
you've seen my answer in the system.

409
00:23:41,408 --> 00:23:42,487
You said that, right?

410
00:23:42,727 --> 00:23:43,767
I mean,

411
00:23:44,848 --> 00:23:47,767
your answer was highly professional.

412
00:23:52,128 --> 00:23:54,648
Is this woman from the consulting firm
for the interview?

413
00:23:55,007 --> 00:23:55,888
Yeah, why?

414
00:24:04,208 --> 00:24:05,727
Interesting. Very funny.

415
00:24:17,567 --> 00:24:18,968
Excuse me, who are you?

416
00:24:22,168 --> 00:24:22,888
Don't you know me?

417
00:24:24,208 --> 00:24:27,087
You came for an interview
without knowing who you're interviewing?

418
00:24:27,487 --> 00:24:28,487
You didn't see my photo?

419
00:24:29,688 --> 00:24:30,648
Dong Yue?

420
00:24:31,208 --> 00:24:31,888
I'm sorry.

421
00:24:32,087 --> 00:24:33,487
Your interview hasn't started yet.

422
00:24:34,007 --> 00:24:35,208
Please wait outside.

423
00:24:35,888 --> 00:24:37,807
I won't wait. I have other things later.

424
00:24:38,007 --> 00:24:39,247
Interview her and me together.

425
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:40,968
But your questions are different.

426
00:24:41,567 --> 00:24:42,327
Isn't that better?

427
00:24:42,327 --> 00:24:43,304
We'll answer our own

428
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:44,408
to avoid copying.

429
00:24:44,848 --> 00:24:45,648
I'm afraid

430
00:24:45,968 --> 00:24:47,688
this might not follow procedure.

431
00:24:48,408 --> 00:24:49,527
Whose procedure?

432
00:24:50,327 --> 00:24:51,448
Your consulting firm's?

433
00:24:56,007 --> 00:24:57,487
If I understand correctly,

434
00:24:57,487 --> 00:25:01,128
we hired your firm to assist us.

435
00:25:01,527 --> 00:25:02,327
So,

436
00:25:03,208 --> 00:25:04,047
you're the vendor.

437
00:25:04,408 --> 00:25:07,168
We're the client. Correct?

438
00:25:09,087 --> 00:25:09,567
Exactly.

439
00:25:09,848 --> 00:25:10,487
That's it.

440
00:25:15,688 --> 00:25:17,007
But if Ms. Zhao minds...

441
00:25:17,007 --> 00:25:17,767
I don't mind.

442
00:25:21,727 --> 00:25:22,408
Let's start.

443
00:25:25,047 --> 00:25:26,007
Can you be professional?

444
00:25:33,968 --> 00:25:36,168
(Guess who's interviewing me today?)

445
00:25:37,527 --> 00:25:38,047
(Who?)

446
00:25:50,007 --> 00:25:51,287
Waiter, check please.

447
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:54,688
Thanks for today.

448
00:25:57,087 --> 00:25:57,848
Not at all.

449
00:25:58,408 --> 00:25:59,168
I'm a good man.

450
00:25:59,807 --> 00:26:00,247
Thank you.

451
00:26:02,767 --> 00:26:03,928
He probably doesn't know.

452
00:26:04,567 --> 00:26:06,408
I think she acted on her own.

453
00:26:06,928 --> 00:26:08,208
You're still defending him?

454
00:26:12,247 --> 00:26:13,087
I don't know either.

455
00:26:14,608 --> 00:26:15,527
I'm confused right now.

456
00:26:19,848 --> 00:26:20,848
I need to be alone.

457
00:26:35,168 --> 00:26:36,287
Want to go for a walk?

458
00:26:48,408 --> 00:26:50,767
This place is kind of my hidden gem.

459
00:26:52,408 --> 00:26:53,848
I won't run into colleagues here.

460
00:26:54,487 --> 00:26:56,047
And I don't see any company products.

461
00:27:00,767 --> 00:27:02,047
(Single Origin Pour-over Coffee)
Pour-over coffee?

462
00:27:03,007 --> 00:27:04,848
Quite tasteful!

463
00:27:12,688 --> 00:27:13,527
What will you have?

464
00:27:13,688 --> 00:27:14,767
Feel free to choose.

465
00:27:16,807 --> 00:27:18,168
I know wine well.

466
00:27:18,168 --> 00:27:20,408
But I don't know pour-over coffee.

467
00:27:21,688 --> 00:27:22,968
Could you pick one for me?

468
00:27:24,567 --> 00:27:26,007
Sure! And you?

469
00:27:26,448 --> 00:27:27,448
The one I had last time.

470
00:27:27,688 --> 00:27:29,527
Okay, just a moment, please.

471
00:27:38,968 --> 00:27:39,327
Thanks.

472
00:27:47,727 --> 00:27:48,448
Girlfriend?

473
00:27:50,208 --> 00:27:51,287
Or lover?

474
00:27:52,448 --> 00:27:55,087
Or confidante?

475
00:27:55,807 --> 00:27:56,928
No. Just a friend.

476
00:27:58,208 --> 00:27:59,208
I don't believe you.

477
00:28:01,767 --> 00:28:04,007
After college,
I signed up for an English class.

478
00:28:04,368 --> 00:28:05,128
We were classmates.

479
00:28:06,968 --> 00:28:07,527
Surprising.

480
00:28:09,247 --> 00:28:10,688
Today, I helped you out.

481
00:28:10,688 --> 00:28:12,448
And I brought you to my special spot.

482
00:28:12,527 --> 00:28:13,544
Is this how you treat me?

483
00:28:14,047 --> 00:28:14,848
That's too much.

484
00:28:16,007 --> 00:28:17,448
Okay, I'm sorry.

485
00:28:23,727 --> 00:28:25,487
But you helped me so much today.

486
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:30,327
Just because you're a good man?

487
00:28:34,448 --> 00:28:35,287
Want the truth?

488
00:28:36,448 --> 00:28:37,047
Of course.

489
00:28:37,848 --> 00:28:40,208
I helped to stir things up.

490
00:28:41,408 --> 00:28:43,047
Make you and your husband fight.

491
00:28:45,527 --> 00:28:46,047
Why?

492
00:28:47,007 --> 00:28:48,487
Your husband and Barry are friends.

493
00:28:50,168 --> 00:28:51,327
If you divorce,

494
00:28:51,848 --> 00:28:53,648
he definitely won't help you anymore.

495
00:28:53,648 --> 00:28:55,047
He might even hold you back.

496
00:28:57,767 --> 00:28:58,767
So the new Sales Director

497
00:29:00,567 --> 00:29:01,168
will be me.

498
00:29:12,247 --> 00:29:13,247
You finally laughed.

499
00:29:13,688 --> 00:29:15,848
You're pretty funny.

500
00:29:21,487 --> 00:29:21,968
Thanks.

501
00:29:31,168 --> 00:29:31,807
Are you local?

502
00:29:34,688 --> 00:29:35,648
To be precise,

503
00:29:35,648 --> 00:29:37,047
I was born in Guangzhou.

504
00:29:37,287 --> 00:29:38,608
But my ancestral home is Huizhou.

505
00:29:40,128 --> 00:29:42,487
My hometown seafood
is incredibly delicious.

506
00:29:42,928 --> 00:29:44,007
You know the mantis shrimp?

507
00:29:44,928 --> 00:29:46,087
This long.

508
00:29:46,287 --> 00:29:47,567
Exceptionally fresh.

509
00:29:47,567 --> 00:29:49,128
Is it that good? I'm getting hungry.

510
00:29:49,727 --> 00:29:50,527
Really.

511
00:29:50,807 --> 00:29:53,247
My whole family loves seafood.

512
00:29:53,727 --> 00:29:55,767
By the way, my family sells dried goods,

513
00:29:55,767 --> 00:29:58,087
like fish maw, dried scallops,

514
00:29:58,087 --> 00:29:58,767
and more.

515
00:29:59,247 --> 00:30:01,047
If you need to buy any,
just let me know.

516
00:30:02,327 --> 00:30:02,807
Sure.

517
00:30:07,247 --> 00:30:07,727
And you?

518
00:30:08,047 --> 00:30:08,608
From Wuhan.

519
00:30:10,007 --> 00:30:10,807
Wuhan?

520
00:30:11,767 --> 00:30:13,688
I've been to Wuhan
on business many times.

521
00:30:14,807 --> 00:30:16,527
There are lots of delicious foods there.

522
00:30:17,007 --> 00:30:18,487
Wuhan duck neck.

523
00:30:18,767 --> 00:30:19,408
Super spicy.

524
00:30:20,327 --> 00:30:23,247
And Sanxian Tofu skin.

525
00:30:23,487 --> 00:30:24,848
Something inside it.

526
00:30:24,848 --> 00:30:25,767
What is it?

527
00:30:25,767 --> 00:30:27,688
Anyway, it's delicious and super fresh.

528
00:30:28,408 --> 00:30:30,007
Maybe we can go to Wuhan together.

529
00:30:30,247 --> 00:30:31,567
We can try the local breakfast.

530
00:30:33,208 --> 00:30:34,888
Just sitting at an old table,

531
00:30:35,128 --> 00:30:36,087
in a rickety chair.

532
00:30:37,327 --> 00:30:38,327
The worst environment

533
00:30:39,487 --> 00:30:40,408
offers the best food.

534
00:30:45,168 --> 00:30:46,247
But I can't get up early.

535
00:30:48,688 --> 00:30:49,567
Can you get up early?

536
00:30:53,208 --> 00:30:54,208
That might be an issue.

537
00:30:57,087 --> 00:30:58,928
I really didn't mean
to interview your wife.

538
00:30:59,688 --> 00:31:00,247
It was Xu Jia.

539
00:31:00,688 --> 00:31:01,727
She said she was too busy.

540
00:31:02,007 --> 00:31:03,047
She asked if I could go.

541
00:31:03,848 --> 00:31:05,247
I already can't finish my reports.

542
00:31:05,608 --> 00:31:07,087
Now I have to do interviews too?

543
00:31:07,928 --> 00:31:09,767
I have an industry conference
this afternoon

544
00:31:10,007 --> 00:31:11,767
and a CPA class tonight.

545
00:31:12,487 --> 00:31:13,727
I can't take it all.

546
00:31:13,888 --> 00:31:14,727
I'm at my limit.

547
00:31:14,968 --> 00:31:16,128
Why not take some time off?

548
00:31:16,888 --> 00:31:19,567
At least, you can find someone else

549
00:31:20,408 --> 00:31:21,368
to interview Zhao Mei.

550
00:31:21,527 --> 00:31:22,287
It's not hard.

551
00:31:22,928 --> 00:31:23,688
It's easy,

552
00:31:23,688 --> 00:31:25,767
but who will be willing to do that?

553
00:31:26,247 --> 00:31:28,047
Who doesn't have a pile of work
right now?

554
00:31:31,327 --> 00:31:32,767
If you're really swamped,

555
00:31:33,208 --> 00:31:34,047
I'll go for you.

556
00:31:35,767 --> 00:31:36,928
Your wife doesn't know me.

557
00:31:37,287 --> 00:31:38,087
So I just...

558
00:31:42,968 --> 00:31:44,608
I really just wanted to help Xu Jia out.

559
00:31:45,448 --> 00:31:48,087
Since when do analysts
help each other out?

560
00:31:50,767 --> 00:31:52,368
I didn't want to help at first.

561
00:31:52,767 --> 00:31:54,848
But you know,
because of what happened with Tao,

562
00:31:55,208 --> 00:31:56,527
they all have issues with me now.

563
00:32:03,047 --> 00:32:04,287
I know I was wrong.

564
00:32:05,408 --> 00:32:08,648
I promise it won't happen again.

565
00:32:09,327 --> 00:32:11,007
Stay away from the GST project.

566
00:32:11,767 --> 00:32:12,968
Work on the Kangya project.

567
00:32:13,567 --> 00:32:15,287
They acquired five hotels in Hubei

568
00:32:15,287 --> 00:32:16,047
to be integrated.

569
00:32:16,047 --> 00:32:16,727
You work on it.

570
00:32:23,208 --> 00:32:23,807
Okay.

571
00:32:25,648 --> 00:32:26,287
Thank you.

572
00:32:28,287 --> 00:32:29,567
For giving me this opportunity.

573
00:32:29,567 --> 00:32:31,247
This isn't an opportunity
but a punishment.

574
00:32:31,247 --> 00:32:32,608
There's no bonus for this project.

575
00:32:32,767 --> 00:32:33,968
I reward you for doing right.

576
00:32:33,968 --> 00:32:35,087
Punish you for doing wrong.

577
00:32:35,168 --> 00:32:36,128
It's a bonus deduction.

578
00:32:36,128 --> 00:32:37,448
If it happens again, you're out!

579
00:32:50,767 --> 00:32:52,128
To thank you for helping me today,

580
00:32:53,648 --> 00:32:54,767
I'll tell you something.

581
00:32:56,208 --> 00:32:59,408
Tang Lide approached me
a couple of days ago.

582
00:32:59,807 --> 00:33:00,567
I heard

583
00:33:01,247 --> 00:33:04,087
the company arranged interviews
for you and Dong Yue.

584
00:33:05,327 --> 00:33:07,408
I fully understand what that means.

585
00:33:08,128 --> 00:33:11,047
It means the next Sales Director

586
00:33:11,368 --> 00:33:13,087
will be either you or Dong Yue.

587
00:33:13,807 --> 00:33:16,047
I like to be direct.

588
00:33:17,767 --> 00:33:19,327
Since I have no hope of promotion,

589
00:33:19,928 --> 00:33:23,527
I'll naturally support someone
I need to support.

590
00:33:25,327 --> 00:33:29,928
I hope my future direct boss is you.

591
00:33:32,327 --> 00:33:33,128
Me?

592
00:33:35,208 --> 00:33:35,767
Why?

593
00:33:36,487 --> 00:33:39,767
Shouldn't your relationship
with Dong Yue be better?

594
00:33:39,968 --> 00:33:40,848
That's personal life.

595
00:33:41,287 --> 00:33:42,527
This is work.

596
00:33:43,128 --> 00:33:46,368
Because our skill sets are different.

597
00:33:46,368 --> 00:33:47,968
You haven't done direct sales.

598
00:33:47,968 --> 00:33:50,527
And in that area, I far surpass you.

599
00:33:50,928 --> 00:33:53,128
Even if you become Sales Director,

600
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:55,487
you'll still need my help.

601
00:33:56,087 --> 00:33:56,727
Besides,

602
00:33:58,047 --> 00:33:59,327
you're a woman.

603
00:34:00,047 --> 00:34:02,007
You'll attend more social events,

604
00:34:02,368 --> 00:34:03,767
like karaoke,

605
00:34:03,767 --> 00:34:05,368
hitting bars, spa party, and such.

606
00:34:05,888 --> 00:34:07,247
To be blunt,

607
00:34:08,047 --> 00:34:12,248
you can't take a sauna with men, right?

608
00:34:13,248 --> 00:34:14,047
So,

609
00:34:14,567 --> 00:34:16,007
you need someone else

610
00:34:16,007 --> 00:34:17,607
to attend these social events.

611
00:34:18,007 --> 00:34:20,248
And it could be me.

612
00:34:23,167 --> 00:34:27,368
Mr. Tang, you mean
your skills overlap with Dong Yue's?

613
00:34:28,047 --> 00:34:28,728
Exactly.

614
00:34:29,768 --> 00:34:31,047
Dong Yue doesn't need me.

615
00:34:31,808 --> 00:34:34,127
Only if you become the Sales Director

616
00:34:34,127 --> 00:34:37,007
will my talents not be wasted.

617
00:34:37,448 --> 00:34:39,567
If Dong Yue becomes Sales Director,

618
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:41,808
I'm telling you right now,

619
00:34:42,448 --> 00:34:44,928
he'll absolutely be a second Xu Yuntian.

620
00:34:46,487 --> 00:34:48,487
I'd be utterly miserable.

621
00:34:54,007 --> 00:34:54,768
Understood.

622
00:34:55,728 --> 00:34:57,607
I have an idea. See if this works.

623
00:34:58,248 --> 00:35:00,408
Aren't you hosting an event at Xincheng?

624
00:35:01,567 --> 00:35:04,328
He wants me
to find a way to sabotage that event.

625
00:35:08,007 --> 00:35:09,808
Xincheng is a new client of mine.

626
00:35:10,408 --> 00:35:12,127
If the first event gets messed up...

627
00:35:13,408 --> 00:35:14,288
Such a ruthless move.

628
00:35:15,848 --> 00:35:16,448
Absolutely.

629
00:35:17,728 --> 00:35:19,007
Since you're honest with me,

630
00:35:19,007 --> 00:35:19,888
I'll be too.

631
00:35:20,968 --> 00:35:22,248
Tang Lide also approached me.

632
00:35:23,808 --> 00:35:24,888
He made me a proposal.

633
00:35:28,328 --> 00:35:29,207
What proposal?

634
00:35:29,448 --> 00:35:30,607
He said he has a way

635
00:35:30,768 --> 00:35:33,368
to make the stores under you
source goods from me to make you fail

636
00:35:34,047 --> 00:35:35,167
to meet your sales target.

637
00:35:37,647 --> 00:35:38,848
Such a cheap shot.

638
00:35:41,167 --> 00:35:43,167
His proposals are rotten, no doubt,

639
00:35:44,487 --> 00:35:46,248
but if he actually succeeds,

640
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:49,127
it'll really hurt both of us.

641
00:35:54,928 --> 00:35:55,928
We can't keep him around.

642
00:35:59,288 --> 00:35:59,928
What do you say?

643
00:36:26,087 --> 00:36:27,687
We got home almost at the same time.

644
00:36:27,687 --> 00:36:28,687
It's quite rare, huh?

645
00:36:30,607 --> 00:36:33,527
Your interview transcripts
are probably already compiled

646
00:36:33,527 --> 00:36:34,607
and sent to your HR.

647
00:36:37,888 --> 00:36:38,647
Have you seen them?

648
00:36:39,968 --> 00:36:41,127
Why would I?

649
00:36:41,328 --> 00:36:42,487
I'm not curious.

650
00:36:43,848 --> 00:36:44,567
To be frank,

651
00:36:44,768 --> 00:36:47,687
the interview is just a formality.

652
00:36:48,647 --> 00:36:51,007
It's just to provide backing
for the boss's choice.

653
00:36:51,848 --> 00:36:55,007
As for who finally gets promoted,
that depends on the boss's preference.

654
00:36:55,647 --> 00:36:56,647
I don't look.

655
00:36:57,047 --> 00:36:58,696
Qi Youlan
and Barry might not look either.

656
00:37:02,248 --> 00:37:04,607
Don't you think it's funny?

657
00:37:05,127 --> 00:37:08,567
Just a couple of days ago,
we talked about whether she was fired.

658
00:37:08,768 --> 00:37:10,487
Today, she came to interview me.

659
00:37:12,647 --> 00:37:15,687
But I remember the person scheduled
to interview me wasn't her.

660
00:37:16,408 --> 00:37:16,928
Really?

661
00:37:18,007 --> 00:37:19,167
I have no clue.

662
00:37:24,728 --> 00:37:25,968
I need a favor from you.

663
00:37:28,288 --> 00:37:30,207
Since Tang Lide
managed the directly-run stores,

664
00:37:30,207 --> 00:37:31,144
sales have been good.

665
00:37:31,607 --> 00:37:32,808
But I've looked at the data.

666
00:37:33,087 --> 00:37:35,728
For the first 20 days each month,
there's almost no sales activity.

667
00:37:36,167 --> 00:37:40,368
But at the end of the month,
a few large orders appear

668
00:37:40,368 --> 00:37:41,408
to push the sales up.

669
00:37:42,728 --> 00:37:45,888
Several times,
this happened on weekday afternoons.

670
00:37:46,808 --> 00:37:49,567
Who buys alcohol on a weekday afternoon?

671
00:37:50,167 --> 00:37:52,808
And these orders don't request invoices.

672
00:37:53,047 --> 00:37:55,647
Clearly, they don't want anyone
to know who bought it.

673
00:37:57,167 --> 00:37:58,888
If I'm not mistaken,

674
00:37:59,888 --> 00:38:03,448
Tang Lide has been using sales funds
to boost the sales of the stores.

675
00:38:05,928 --> 00:38:07,007
So what do you plan to do?

676
00:38:09,248 --> 00:38:12,368
I want you to help me get Barry
to the directly-run stores.

677
00:38:15,047 --> 00:38:16,328
He's a suspicious person.

678
00:38:16,928 --> 00:38:18,687
He only believes what he sees.

679
00:38:19,527 --> 00:38:21,167
The food at this restaurant is good,

680
00:38:21,167 --> 00:38:22,487
but I didn't enjoy the drinks.

681
00:38:22,768 --> 00:38:23,848
It is the weekend.

682
00:38:23,848 --> 00:38:25,487
Let's go somewhere else and drink.

683
00:38:25,728 --> 00:38:26,848
Okay, let's drink!

684
00:38:26,848 --> 00:38:27,567
Name a place.

685
00:38:28,207 --> 00:38:29,167
Barry's the connoisseur.

686
00:38:29,167 --> 00:38:29,928
Let Barry decide.

687
00:38:31,087 --> 00:38:32,288
If I had to choose,

688
00:38:33,207 --> 00:38:35,207
I'd prefer somewhere quieter.

689
00:38:35,848 --> 00:38:36,888
Like a whiskey club.

690
00:38:39,848 --> 00:38:40,408
Barry,

691
00:38:40,768 --> 00:38:43,207
isn't that your company's store?

692
00:38:43,487 --> 00:38:46,647
Right!
I almost forgot we have a store here.

693
00:38:46,888 --> 00:38:48,047
But I'm not sure.

694
00:38:48,167 --> 00:38:50,607
On a Saturday night, it's probably full.

695
00:38:51,167 --> 00:38:51,808
Barry,

696
00:38:52,047 --> 00:38:53,207
you're the boss.

697
00:38:55,167 --> 00:38:56,167
Let's go check it out.

698
00:38:58,567 --> 00:39:00,487
Even if Barry goes there,

699
00:39:00,487 --> 00:39:03,487
how can you guarantee
that Tang Lide's people will be buying

700
00:39:03,487 --> 00:39:05,408
right when Barry walks in?

701
00:39:09,127 --> 00:39:10,087
What's going on?

702
00:39:11,007 --> 00:39:12,207
There are no customers here.

703
00:39:12,728 --> 00:39:14,047
It is a bit empty.

704
00:39:15,047 --> 00:39:16,248
This is impossible!

705
00:39:16,848 --> 00:39:18,328
Their business is doing quite well.

706
00:39:18,808 --> 00:39:20,527
Their sales reached 1.1 million
last month.

707
00:39:20,928 --> 00:39:23,368
That means nearly 300,000 weekly.

708
00:39:24,047 --> 00:39:25,647
Each weekend brought in 150,000.

709
00:39:26,567 --> 00:39:29,047
But regardless,
it shouldn't be like this.

710
00:39:30,007 --> 00:39:30,647
This way.

711
00:39:31,687 --> 00:39:34,248
Barry, someone's buying liquor.

712
00:39:35,408 --> 00:39:36,687
What would you like to drink?

713
00:39:37,607 --> 00:39:38,167
What to drink?

714
00:39:38,728 --> 00:39:40,207
A bottle of 25-year-old Gennadiy.

715
00:39:40,207 --> 00:39:41,328
Please wait a moment.

716
00:39:41,328 --> 00:39:41,808
Hold on.

717
00:39:45,087 --> 00:39:46,288
Is he buying liquor?

718
00:39:47,328 --> 00:39:47,728
Yes.

719
00:39:49,368 --> 00:39:50,087
That much?

720
00:39:51,487 --> 00:39:52,567
Okay, no problem.

721
00:39:52,607 --> 00:39:53,408
96 bottles in total.

722
00:39:53,408 --> 00:39:54,248
I'll scan your code.

723
00:39:57,328 --> 00:39:58,167
Business is slow,

724
00:39:58,167 --> 00:39:59,647
but the sales are impressive.

725
00:39:59,808 --> 00:40:01,047
Buying 96 bottles at once.

726
00:40:02,288 --> 00:40:05,728
This must be
for a wedding or corporate event.

727
00:40:05,888 --> 00:40:06,527
Careful.

728
00:40:10,928 --> 00:40:11,728
Thank you.

729
00:40:12,248 --> 00:40:13,487
You're welcome. Enjoy.

730
00:40:14,248 --> 00:40:14,768
Barry.

731
00:40:15,647 --> 00:40:16,207
Barry?

732
00:40:17,007 --> 00:40:17,527
What's wrong?

733
00:40:17,808 --> 00:40:18,808
Something feels off.

734
00:40:19,527 --> 00:40:20,087
What's off?

735
00:40:20,768 --> 00:40:21,768
This is a bar.

736
00:40:23,207 --> 00:40:25,968
How could anyone buy 96 bottles
from a bar?

737
00:40:26,167 --> 00:40:28,408
Besides, we have online stores
and delivery services.

738
00:40:29,087 --> 00:40:30,808
That guy bought 96 bottles

739
00:40:31,207 --> 00:40:32,448
and picked them up personally.

740
00:40:32,848 --> 00:40:33,848
How is that possible?

741
00:40:36,527 --> 00:40:38,167
I hadn't noticed until you mentioned it.

742
00:40:38,207 --> 00:40:39,047
That's strange.

743
00:40:42,328 --> 00:40:45,207
I don't know
when Tang Lide's people will go buy,

744
00:40:46,167 --> 00:40:50,848
but I can send someone
to buy whenever I want.

745
00:40:59,047 --> 00:41:00,928
Okay.

746
00:41:02,288 --> 00:41:03,007
It's already done.

747
00:41:04,687 --> 00:41:05,768
Is this guy reliable?

748
00:41:06,527 --> 00:41:07,087
Don't worry.

749
00:41:07,087 --> 00:41:08,328
I've known him for years.

750
00:41:09,288 --> 00:41:10,007
He is clever.

751
00:41:29,723 --> 00:41:34,463
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

752
00:41:38,913 --> 00:41:40,833
♪Too much of shame♪

753
00:41:41,179 --> 00:41:43,975
♪To waste it crying♪

754
00:41:46,433 --> 00:41:48,353
♪Leave all behind you♪

755
00:41:48,353 --> 00:41:50,633
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

756
00:41:50,753 --> 00:41:52,982
♪You know how far you've gone♪

757
00:41:53,117 --> 00:41:55,393
♪In the fire you rise again♪

758
00:41:55,579 --> 00:41:57,939
♪You made it through the worst♪

759
00:41:58,077 --> 00:42:00,281
♪The best is yet to come♪

760
00:42:00,524 --> 00:42:02,664
♪The best is yet to come♪

761
00:42:05,366 --> 00:42:06,689
♪Isn't it magical♪

762
00:42:06,689 --> 00:42:08,321
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

763
00:42:08,353 --> 00:42:10,820
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

764
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:13,273
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

765
00:42:13,354 --> 00:42:16,002
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

766
00:42:16,091 --> 00:42:18,622
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

767
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:20,924
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

768
00:42:21,066 --> 00:42:22,147
♪But I don't want to♪

769
00:42:22,256 --> 00:42:24,522
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

770
00:42:24,638 --> 00:42:25,703
♪Until 3 AM♪

771
00:42:25,874 --> 00:42:27,079
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

772
00:42:27,233 --> 00:42:28,466
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

773
00:42:28,557 --> 00:42:30,921
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

774
00:42:31,068 --> 00:42:35,478
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

775
00:42:50,203 --> 00:42:51,639
♪Leave all behind you♪

776
00:42:51,743 --> 00:42:54,230
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

777
00:42:54,413 --> 00:42:56,542
♪You know how far you've gone♪

778
00:42:56,729 --> 00:42:59,069
♪In the fire you rise again♪

779
00:42:59,137 --> 00:43:01,403
♪You made it through the worst♪

780
00:43:01,763 --> 00:43:03,841
♪The best is yet to come♪

781
00:43:04,090 --> 00:43:06,260
♪The best is yet to come♪

782
00:43:08,961 --> 00:43:10,113
♪Isn't it magical♪

783
00:43:10,113 --> 00:43:13,759
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

784
00:43:13,793 --> 00:43:15,649
♪And I see them sparkling♪

785
00:43:15,873 --> 00:43:18,004
♪Nobody knows♪

786
00:43:18,625 --> 00:43:20,535
♪What tomorrow brings♪

787
00:43:20,801 --> 00:43:23,124
♪You made it through the worst♪

788
00:43:23,311 --> 00:43:25,519
♪The best is yet to come♪

789
00:43:25,806 --> 00:43:27,955
♪The best is yet to come♪

790
00:43:28,251 --> 00:43:29,665
♪Isn't it magical♪

791
00:43:29,665 --> 00:43:31,877
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

792
00:43:31,951 --> 00:43:34,305
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

793
00:43:34,305 --> 00:43:35,393
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

794
00:43:35,393 --> 00:43:38,844
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

795
00:43:39,297 --> 00:43:41,571
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

796
00:43:41,985 --> 00:43:42,849
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

797
00:43:42,849 --> 00:43:44,369
♪Isn't it magical♪
